The SJS Management is excited to host “Children’s Cancer Celebration” and raffle fundraiser benefiting the Children’s Healthcare of Atlanta (CHOA). All proceeds from this event will benefit childhood cancer prevention, awareness and education throughout our communities. The Children’s Cancer Celebration will start at 7:00PM in the Oglethorpe Hospitality Suite at the Columbus Civic Center during the April 20th Columbus Lions Arena Football Cancer Awareness Game. The raffle winners will be selected during halftime at The Columbus Lions Arena Football Cancer Awareness Game which kicks off at 7:30 PM against the Richmond Raiders. Game and raffle tickets can be purchased on https://childrenscancercelebration..com.

Raffle tickets can be purchased for $10 and the prizes include a Masterbuilt Electric Smoker, Beats by Dre Headphones (Studio Version), Beauty Bag with Cosmetics and 2 packs of Remy Hair, Authentic Columbus Lions Football Autographed by the Players and a $50 Spa Gift Card. WINNERS DO NOT HAVE TO BE PRESENT TO WIN!

Participants in the Children’s Cancer Celebration will dine in the Oglethorpe Hospitality Suite during the April 20th Columbus Lions Arena Football game. The Columbus Lions Players will wear custom designed jerseys and play with Pink Footballs which will be auctioned off to the highest bidder after the game to benefit The John B. Amos Cancer Center and Children’s Healthcare of Atlanta (CHOA).

As a not-for-profit healthcare organization, CHOA relies on the philanthropic and volunteer support of the community to provide the high-quality care that all children deserve. They are committed to spending wisely the gifts they receive because they recognize the significance of our decision to give to CHOA. We are truly fortunate to help support the children treated at Children's Healthcare of Atlanta.

Attached are a summary of donation opportunities outlining how you and your organization can help. Partners are needed to provide the resources to help the CHOA raise awareness and implement prevention strategies within our community that will help children affect by Cancer. Even if you are unable to meet the donation levels listed, donations at any amount are always appreciated.

 We would like to thank you in advance for any support you are able to provide CHOA.

What's Holding YOU Back

From The Life You Dream About?

 

 

Don't Allow Default to Determine Your Destiny

 

 The Next By Design 6 week Challenge BEGINS:

 THURSDAYS - May 23 - June 27 (7-930pm)


In today's non-stop world, with the heavy demands of work, jumbo mortgages, never-ending bills, managing a home and the dynamics of relationships, how many of us find that we are always attending to the URGENT and neglecting the IMPORTANT because of a lack of time?  

LIVING BY DESIGN is about making the time to make the change in the little things that have the greatest impact on our lives.  The daily decisions that determine where we are headed.  The choices we make that reveal our priorities.  The default behaviors we resort to that sabatoge our future and our core values.  

During the LIVE IT BY DESIGN 6 Week Challenge you will discover and design your own journey towards lasting change.  By Design will give you practical tools that will affect your health, finances, home, business and your relationships.  You will MAKE THE TIME to set your sights on where you want to go and you will create your plan on how you can get there. 

You'll learn a simple yet powerful sytem that will show you how to create the life you want according to your unique design.  

 

At The Live It By Design 6 Week Challenge  

Discover...

  • How to find the hidden keys to motivation and living your best life now 
  • Secrets to moving past the boundaries of your past choices, your family dynamics, your environment, your track record and your personal beliefs
  • Learn simple strategies how to live by design in your health, home, time, finances, family, workplace and your community

  • Increase your influence, your income and your impact on the community
  • Break through the limiting beliefs that have held you back from living with confidence

During these fun-filled workshops, the BY DESIGN team will share a step-by-step method that has the potential to radically affect your daily life & habits and give you the ability to help others do the same.  It's the little things that happen everyday that will affect the course of your life.  

You will leave with renewed confidence to make a difference in your community.  You will find motivation you never knew you had and be inspired by the stories of those around you.  

Advance your life skills, build relationships and impact your world for change.  If you are looking to retreat - this is NOT the place for you.

Live It By Design is a game changer.  You will find it difficult to keep your results to yourself, and will want to share it with everyone you know.

 

MISC TERMS:   An ethics agreement and release & acknowlegment form will be required upon registration. No children allowed in the seminar.  Participants will be responsible for their own  beverages. 

 


 Attend Risk Free!

If you attend this event and are not pleased with your experience, we will give you a 100% refund!  Your Order is 100% Guaranteed!    


Recent Live It By Design Stories

 

"Before Live It By Design I was extremely skeptical when introduced to the idea of personal development and pretty uninterested when my wife asked me if I would be willing to attend.  I was aprehensive and had a pretty closed mind.  I mean, no one likes to hear their life needs improvement right, least of all me.  I had all the answers and advice my clients needed to hear to solve their problems and relationships, but my own relationship was going down the tubes.   We learned that we are not alone, that there are other people out there just like us who just need to be encouraged and pointed back in the right direction, people who need their hearts spoken to and life spoken over them.  I recommend this program to anyone having any doubt about the direction you are heading in life, or anyone at an impasse in your relationships with family or your significant other.  This isn't a quick fix program, it's a life long journey.  If you apply yourself to it, you will see results, you will learn valuable life skills and you will meet some of the most amazing, uplifting, real and genuine people, that will fill your heart with inspiration, energy and hope!  Be prepared for a life changing experience, and keep an open mind.  You won't be disappointed! 

Mike Hewett


"Before the Live It By Design Challenge, I knew where I wanted to go, but I just wasnt' getting there.  Attending By Design made all the difference for me.  How people were so energized to do more in their lives and see change, that motivated me to put into action a lot of stuff I already knew but wasn't doing."

Rolf de Geest


"I hit a wall before we started this process.  All I could do was keep my head above water.  Before Live It By Design, all I was doing was standing.  But I was like, take a first step and see what happens.  Since applying what I’ve learned, my husband has seen change in me, and my coworkers have seen change in me, my friends have seen change in me and it’s just starting out.  I’m just really excited about where this is heading.”

“It’s like little tiny mindsets that have changed in every aspect of my life.  And now I feel like I’m unstoppable, like there are so many things that I can do.  Instead of what can’t I do, there’s so many things I can do.”

HTML5's Best-Kept Secret: Using Microdata to Improve Your Search Results // TECH 754

Alexis Goldstein, Author, HTML5 & CSS3 for the Real World

Tuesday, July 5th, from 6:00 pm to 7:30 pm.

Microdata is an often-ignored mechanism of HTML5 that allows a page to be "seen" more clearly by Google. It allows users to define page content using vocabulary that can be easily recognized by Google’s search function and incorporated into Google search results. Microdata can be used to designate an official URL, a bio pic, and product images, and to distinguish these from other page content. And because Microdata is a less-hyped feature of HTML5, your competitors may not have added it.

This course will provide students with a working understanding of Microdata. It will teach the various vocabularies used to better describe a page to search engines, whether it’s for a person, organization, product, or offer, and give real examples of how to add Microdata to existing pages.

Use the hashtag #gamicrodata to ask follow-up questions and continue the conversation.

Can't make it? Sign up at http://generalassemb.ly to stay in the loop on future events and classes.

Important Update: Due to enormous demand for the event we have oversold the capacity of our original location, and have thus moved the location to accomodate everyone. The new location is at OCAD University; address is in the right sidebar.


If you are in high school and applying to universities, you're probably really confused about the whole process and about which schools you should be applying to. Ever tried going to a university fair? You wait 20 minutes in line to talk to a recruiter at a booth and they give you nothing but fluff and marketing ploys that don’t answer your questions.

There is a better solution. The Atlas Symposium brings the top 3rd/4th year students from Waterloo, Queen's Commerce, Ivey (University of Western Ontario), and Schulich (York U) to debate each other on stage in October in downtown Toronto to impart their firsthand experiences--no BS, no marketing fluff. Just straight and to-the-point insider information that exposes all the facts about the schools you are looking to attend.

Even when you think you know where you are going, there is so much insider information and nuance going on behind the scenes between universities, corporate recruiters, and inter-school politics that the vast majority of high school students don't even realize what the details are.

The Atlas Symposium will be the place to dig up all the dirt on the top universities; you'll have access to information that won't be found anywhere else--all for the price of a large latte or cup of coffee from your favourite coffeeshop.

The culture of a student body is arguably one of the most important factors to consider when choosing a school. Why drive across the province to in order to get a sense of the culture of each campus when you can come to the Atlas Symposium?

Your future is important. Why make a decision about what school to attend without first having the information that you deserve to know?


Get your ticket today before we run out of space!



Feel free to check out our Facebook page: http://facebook.com/AtlasSymposium

The Genealogical Society of Pennsylvania and Ancestry.com are pleased to welcome you to

 

PENNSYLVANIA FAMILY HISTORY DAY

Join GSP and Ancestry.com along with other leaders in the genealogical community for a full day of lectures and workshops.

 

While you are registering you will be requested to choose from a variety of lecture topics for each time slot, including:

 

9:30 - 10:30 AM

Ancestry Track: Getting Started with Ancestry.com with Juliana Smith

Methodology: Immigrant Cluster Communities with Lisa Alzo

Pennsylvania: Researching Pennsylvania Ancestors with John Humphrey

 

11:00 AM - Noon

Ancestry Track: Dead Men Do Tell Tales with Lou Szucs

Methodology: What Constitutes a Reasonably Exhaustive Search with Michael Hait

Pennsylvania: Formation of the Pennsylvania Counties with Susan Koelble

 

1:45 - 2:45

Ancestry Track: Finding Your US Military Heroes on Ancestry.com with Juliana Smith

Methodology: Visualizing the Past: Maps and Genealogy with Shamele Jordon

Pennsylvania: Pennsylvania's Land Records with John Humphrey

 

3:00 - 4:00

Ancestry Track: Hidden Treasures at Ancestry.com with Lou Szucs

Methodology: Mining the Motherlode: Using Periodical Literature for Genealogical Research with Curt Witcher

Pennsylvania: Using the Pennsylvania State Archives and Library with Kathleen Hale and Aaron McWilliams


For those just starting out to the seasoned genealogist, the lecture schedule includes subjects sure to interest every research level. Don't miss this unique opportunity to see and talk with some of the nation's top genealogy speakers in one place.


Click here for the full schedule and presenter bios.  (Please review the course list and select your preferred classes, as you'll be asked to note them when you complete your registration.)


Also visit vendor tables, browse the latest in genealogy publications, and talk with exhibitors from national and local genealogical organizations. Vendors currently include Ancestor Tracks, Retrospect Publishing, Reel Tributes, Laurel Hill Cemetery, and PA Genealogy Books, with more to come!

 

There will also be a pre-conference event Friday night at the hotel from 7 to 9 pm that is free with your conference registration. Ask a Pennsylvania expert your research question, meet and mingle with other attendees, and enjoy appetizers compliments of GSP. Cash bar will be available.

 

Presenters

Ancestry.com staff:

Loretto "Lou" Szucs, CGL, FUGA -  Vice President of Community Relations for The Generations Network, involved in the genealogical community for more than 30 years as a researcher, lecturer and writer. She is also the author of They Became Americans: Finding Naturalization Records and Ethnic Origins.

Juliana Smith - Senior Communications and Education Marketing Associate at Ancestry.com and editor of Ancestry Weekly Discovery.

 

Additional presentations by:

Lisa A. Alzo - genealogist, writer for Family Tree magazine, and author of nine books, including Finding Your Slovak Ancestors. 

Michael Hait, CG - column contributor to the African American Genealogy Examiner and author of The Family History Research Toolkit.

Kathleen Hale - Supervisor for Public Services and Digital Imaging Project Manager at the State Library of Pennsylvania.

John T. Humphrey, CG  - genealogical researcher, writer of numerous books including Understanding and Using Baptismal Records and a 14-volume set of Pennsylvania births.

Shamele Jordon - an accomplished researcher who worked on the PBS series Oprah's Roots, and is former president of the African American Genealogy Group.

Susan Koelble - longtime Pennsylvania researcher and lecturer.

Aaron McWilliams - Archivist at Pennsylvania State Archives, worked with NBC show Who Do You Think You Are? to help actor Steve Buscemi find his Pennsylvania roots.

Pat Richley - (a.k.a. DearMYRTLE) - author of hundreds of blogs, columns and magazine articles under her nom de plume.  She is also a vice president of the Utah Genealogical Association.

Curt B. Witcher, MLS, FUGA - Manager of the Genealogy Center at the Allen County Public Library and VP of Development on the board of the Federation of Genealogical Societies.

 

~~~~

Registration: 

GSP members receive a $20 discount on conference registration! 

Not a member and want to sign up? Join on our membership page:

GSP Membership Page.


Registration is $75 for GSP members, $95 for non-members. Space is limited, so register as soon as possible. Lunch is included in registration fee.

(Please note that when registering online, you'll be asked which lectures you'd like to attend.  This does not commit you to a particular lecture, it simply helps us when determining room space for presentations.)

If you prefer to pay by check, until October 1 you can mail your registration fee to:  Genealogical Society of Pennsylvania, 2207 Chestnut Street, Philadelphia, PA 19103 . Please print the November 5 schedule and circle which lectures you would like to attend, and include your contact information, including email address and phone number.


Accommodations:

 

The conference hotel rate is $119. Mention the Genealogical Society of Pennsylvania when booking your room to get this special rate, or use group code 11056794TH.  Conference registration check-in opens Saturday, November 5 at 7:30 AM.

 

Parking and transportation:

Parking is free in the hotel lot. The Philadelphia International Airport is a short 45 minute drive from the conference site. If you need directions to the Wyndham Gardens conference center please visit their website here.

 

Local attractions:

Exton, PA, is located in the Brandywine Valley of Chester County, which includes a variety of historical sites and attractions, including Valley Forge National Park, the Chester County Historical Society and more.  In addition, there are outlet malls and fine shopping, world-class restaurants, and attractions like Longwood Gardens and the Brandywine River Museum and battlefields. Philadelphia and all of its history and culture is less than an hour away. Come for the whole weekend and explore!


Refunds:

With extenuating circumstances, refunds will be issued minus a $20 administrative fee up til October 1.   After October 1, no refunds will be issued.

Speaking on your feet: an advanced workshop on impromptu speaking

  

Do you worry about the Q & A session at the end of your presentation? Do you freeze when asked a difficult question in public? Do you wish you could instantly find convincing arguments to defend your opinions? The good news is that having the mental agility to give articulate responses to unexpected questions is a skill that can be learnt.

  

After his successful classes at JCI London on impromptu speaking, David Jones returns with an advanced workshop. During this highly interactive and fast-paced workshop you will present in a range of different impromptu speaking situations. You will grow in confidence and skill by getting lots of practical experience and feedback. You will practice how to (1) develop and express ideas while on stage, (2) debate from both sides of an argument, (3) answer rapid-fire questions, and (4) speak on any subject thrown at you.

  

David Jones has been writing and presenting training courses since 1996. He teaches a range of transferable skills but is most passionate about helping people improve their public speaking. David has numerous public speaking awards, and has won the Toastmasters’ UK & Ireland Impromptu Speech championship three times in the last eight years.

Live Online - MarkLogic Server Essentials

*Time Zone for the Class: Central Time (USA)*

 

Live Online learning is the perfect solution for those who want to attend MarkLogic courses but are unable to travel. Our expert instructors deliver the same high-quality courses with the same hands-on lab experiences as our traditional classroom courses - minus the travel. Participants need to provide a computer as well as phone and internet access - class starts at 9am Central Time.

 

MarkLogic Server Essentials is a 3-day hands-on course that provides developers with the essentials they need to create web applications using MarkLogic Server. This is a project-based course that focuses on hands-on exercises and the development of a fully functional application. Students walk away with a firm grasp of the concepts essential for developing applications on MarkLogic Server.

Unit 1: Understanding MarkLogic Server
Unit 2: Setting up MarkLogic Server
Unit 3: Constructing an HTTP Application
Unit 4: Loading Content into a Database
Unit 5: Creating XQuery Files
Unit 6: Creating a Basic Search
Unit 7: Working with Indexes
Unit 8: Snippets, Highlighting, Sorting, and Pagination
Unit 9: Organizing Application Files and Code
Unit 10: Creating Faceted Navigation
Unit 11: Creating an Advanced Search
Unit 12: Updating Database Content
Unit 13: Assigning Application Security

Appendix A: Troubleshooting Techniques
Appendix B: Creating a WebDAV Server
Appendix C: Installing XQDT for Eclipse

Recommended Prerequisites: XQuery, any application server technology, HTML/CSS

Required Equipment: Students will need a laptop for which they have administrator permissions, running Windows natively or in a virtualized environment as well as phone and internet access. For system requirements, please see http://developer.marklogic.com/products/marklogic-server/requirements.

Terms & Conditions: MarkLogic Corp. must receive a valid Purchase Order or full payment prior to the start of the course. MarkLogic Corp. reserves the right to cancel courses up to 10 working days prior to the published start date. Please consider this when making your travel plans as MarkLogic's liability is limited to a full refund of tuition only.

We recognize that cancellations are sometimes unavoidable. Participants who notify MarkLogic in writing at least 10 days prior to the start date of a course are entitled to a full tuition refund. Participants who cancel within the 10-day period before the course start date will be eligible for a 50% tuition refund. Participants who register and fail to attend the course are not eligible for a refund. Substitution candidates are acceptable if MarkLogic is notified in writing of the change.

About MarkLogic University: MarkLogic University provides a variety of courses to enable developers, administrators, and product managers to take full advantage of the benefits of MarkLogic products. Courses are designed to deliver deep knowledge of MarkLogic products, toolkits, and connectors, including best practices around design, development and maintenance of an application.

The Live It By Design Team is a network of highly motivated entrepreneurs and educators equipping people of all ages with tried & true skills, motivation and the tools needed to design your life from the inside out.  

By Design will help you discover your internal beliefs about your time, your money, your health, your relationships, your work and your contribution to the world.  Discussing everything from grocery lists, healthy habits, simple building blocks for business, managing family dynamics & creating mission statements, this interactive, fun-filled weekend is packed with activities guaranteed to get you moving & impact those around you.  This team is committed to delivering practical tips & stories that have the power to change your daily direction and in turn, change your life. 

You will learn a simple but powerful system that will show you how to take responsibility and create the life you want according to your unique design, in a community that will keep you motivated and inspired to stay on course and follow through on your dreams.  

We look forward to seeing you at the next event!
org_desc.4: General Assembly is a campus for technology, design, and entrepreneurship. We provide educational programming, space, and support to facilitate collaborative practices and learning opportunities across a community inspired by the entrepreneurial experience.
org_desc.5: The Mobile Marketing Association (MMA) is the premier global non-profit trade association representing all players in the mobile marketing value chain. With more than 700 member companies, the MMA is an action-oriented organization with global focus, regional actions and local relevance. The MMA's primary focus is to establish mobile as an indispensible part of the marketing mix. The MMA works to promote, educate, measure, guide and protect the mobile marketing industry worldwide. The MMA's global headquarters are located in the United States and it has regional chapters including North America (NA), Europe, Middle East and Africa (EMEA), Latin America (LATAM), and Asia Pacific (APAC) branches. For more information, please visit www.mmaglobal.com.
org_desc.10: Founded in 1892 as a non-profit organization, the Genealogical Society of Pennsylvania (GSP) was among the first in the United States to recognize the value of collecting and preserving the vital and personal records of those ancestors whose lives now comprise our American History. GSP is committed to preserving and publishing heretofore unpublished primary sources. The continuing dedication to this service enables the Society to make an increasingly significant contribution to the cultural life of our city, state, and indeed the whole country.
org_desc.11: Junior Chamber International (JCI) is a dynamic and global organisation that is creating positive change by developing the leaders of the future. We deliver innovative and exciting programmes, enhancing citizenship, fellowship and self-development leading to sustainable success in your life, organisation and society.
